      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>When the following alcohol is treated with POCl<sub>3</sub> and pyridine, the expected elimination product is formed. However, when the same alcohol is treated with H<sub>2</sub>SO<sub>4</sub>, the elimination product is 1,2-dimethylcyclopentene. Propose a mechanism for each pathway to account for these differences.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBdFVWIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--84bd95feffe57cc75b7f27e90ac1419de487189b/OChem_17_EC_028.jpg\" alt=\"Propan-2-ylidenecyclobutane reacts with 2-cyclobutylpropan-2-ol. This reacts with sulfuric acid to form 1,2-dimethylcyclopent-1-ene.\">",
